🎞️ Pinned Scene: “Two Unfinished Things”

[INT. PRIVATE ART GALLERY – HAWTHORN ESTATE – NIGHT]

The gallery has thinned. The important conversations have drifted toward wine and whispers. The sculpture remains where it is — still waiting.

The Toreador neonate hasn’t moved much. He’s learned not to. Moving looks like need.

A shape resolves at the edge of the light.

Not dramatic. Just present.

PHREAK stands just outside the sculpture’s pool of illumination, hands folded loosely, head tilted in consideration. The sodium-and-gold lighting treats him poorly. He doesn’t notice.

He studies the sculpture with genuine interest.

A long beat.

PHREAK: “You stopped before it lied.”

The Toreador blinks, startled — not by Phreak’s appearance, but by the comment. Someone actually looked.

TOREADOR: “I… didn’t want to finish it wrong.”

Phreak nods, satisfied. He steps closer, fingers briefly catching the light as they trace the air near the marble — never touching.

PHREAK: “Yeah. Everyone thinks unfinished means incomplete. Sometimes it just means honest.”

The Toreador glances at Phreak’s face now — registers something — then pushes past it, because the moment matters more.

TOREADOR: “Do you really think that?”

PHREAK: “Absolutely.”
(beat)
“Systems break when you force closure too early.”

He smiles, quick and reflexive. The shadow behind him does not.

The Toreador smiles back — tentative, grateful.

For a moment, neither of them realizes what the other is.

They’re just two things waiting to be understood.

[CUT TO BLACK]